ZH: 昨天，他骑马堕马了。
EN: Yesterday, he fell off the horse while riding.

ZH: 他由于堕马而受了轻伤。
EN: He got slightly injured from falling off the horse.

ZH: 这个剧场里曾经有一场壮观的堕马表演。
EN: There was once a spectacular horse-riding stunt show in this theater.

ZH: 骑手艰难地避免了一场堕马事故。
EN: The rider narrowly avoided a horse-riding accident.

ZH: 他的尽责让他得以成功地防止堕马。
EN: His diligence allowed him to successfully prevent falling off the horse.

ZH: 这个公司的堕马率非常低。
EN: The company has a very low horse-riding accident rate.

ZH: 他的坚定决心使他能够克服堕马的恐惧。
EN: His determination allowed him to overcome the fear of falling off a horse.

ZH: 堕马并没有削弱她对马术的热情。
EN: Falling off the horse didn't dampen her enthusiasm for horseback riding.

ZH: 骑手们都接受过严格的堕马防范培训。
EN: The riders have all undergone rigorous training to prevent falling off the horse.

ZH: 他因为堕马而暂时失去了骑马的信心。
EN: He temporarily lost his confidence in horseback riding due to falling off the horse.

ZH: 骑手们都必须戴着头盔来防止堕马时受伤。
EN: The riders must wear helmets to prevent injuries from falling off the horse.

ZH: 这位骑手在堕马后休息了几天。
EN: The rider took a few days off to rest after falling off the horse.

ZH: 堕马是骑马运动中的一种危险情况。
EN: Falling off the horse is a dangerous situation in horseback riding.

ZH: 他在堕马后没有受伤，真是幸运。
EN: He was lucky to not be injured after falling off the horse.

ZH: 这位骑手每次堕马后总是能快速地重新上马。
EN: This rider always manages to get back on the horse quickly after falling off.

ZH: 她因为堕马而失去了对骑马的兴趣。
EN: She lost interest in horseback riding after falling off the horse.

ZH: 他在堕马后感到不安和紧张。
EN: He felt uneasy and nervous after falling off the horse.

ZH: 堕马是骑马时的一个自然风险。
EN: Falling off the horse is a natural risk in horseback riding.

ZH: 尽管堕马会带来伤害，但这并不减少人们对马术的热爱。
EN: Despite the potential harm from falling off the horse, it doesn't diminish people's love for horseback riding.

ZH: 这位骑手已经克服了过去的堕马经历。
EN: This rider has overcome their past experiences of falling off the horse.

ZH: 堕马是他们之间的共同经历，让他们更加团结。
EN: Falling off the horse is a shared experience among them, making them more united.
